# 🖼️ Image Resizer & Converter Tool

A simple Python script to **batch resize** or **enlarge** images and convert them to **PNG** format.  
Built with **Python** and **Pillow**.

---

## 📌 Features
- Resize **or enlarge** images in bulk
- Automatically creates `input_images` and `output_images` folders
- Converts all images to **PNG**
- Handles errors gracefully (skips non-image files)
- Works in **Python IDLE**, Wing IDE, or any terminal

---

## 📂 Folder Structure
│
├── image_resizer.py # Main Python script
├── input_images/ # Place your input images here
├── output_images/ # Processed images will be saved here
└── README.md # Project documentation

## ⚙️ Requirements

### 1. Install Python  
Download and install **Python 3.x** from:  
[https://www.python.org/downloads/](https://www.python.org/downloads/)  
Make sure to check **"Add Python to PATH"** during installation.

### 2. Install Pillow  
Pillow is the Python library used for image processing.

#### 💻 Windows  
Open **Command Prompt** and run:  
